<TITLE> HuJI financier in 5 day remand </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 21 (bdnews24.com) A court gave the police 5 days to question Golam Mostafa, an alleged financier of Harkatul Jihad al Islami (HuJI). Mostafa was produced at the Chief Metropolitan Magistrates court on Wednesday after a four day remand under section 54. The Detective Branch appealed for 10 more days of remand for questioning Mostofa in a case with Hazaribag Police Station filed under the anti-terrorism act. Nazrul Islam, the judge, granted five days after hearing the plea. Ratan Sheikh, a general recording officer and sub-inspector of police in the court, confirmed bdnews24.com of the remand. Mostafa, a Bangladeshi British citizen, has been working to strengthen a number of militant outfits including HuJI. He was allegedly preparing for large-scale destructives activities. Mostafa was taken into remand for questioning for four days on April 17. 
